The publicity agency for a famous family tracks how many retweets each tweet receives. All tweets from May 4th to October 3rd were analyzed. The amount of retweets (in thousands) is summarized below.
Minimum Q$_1$ Median Q$_3$ Maximum
@Chloe 47 54 72 82 103
@Cylie 45 77 83 91 105
@Cendall 32 37 66 95 256


Which statement is true?

Careem is learning about randomness in his AP Statistics class. His teacher has him roll a six-sided number cube four times and record the results. He repeats this process for a total of four trials. Here are his results:
Trial $1$: {$1$, $6$, $1$, $6$}
Trial $2$: {$1$, $2$, $3$, $4$}
Trial $3$: {$4$, $4$, $4$, $4$}
Trial $4$: {$2$, $5$, $6$, $1$}
Which trial was the most random?
